    "body": "I am quite sure it does not work for me.\r\n  On one hand I would have to change the call from the neat and comfy `tx = await someContract.fun( arg1, arg2);` to call the RPC directly via `await hre.network.provider.request` I guess.\r\n  \r\n  But what is most suspicious is that `await ethers.provider.getBlock(await ethers.provider.getBlockNumber())` has only the last fine/non-reverting transaction and the reverted one seems nowhere to be queried.\r\n  \r\n( I have checked that --version I have is `2.3.0`. )\r\n",
