    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@Huge My guess is that what's happening to you is that ethers.js first sends an `eth_estimateGas` call, and if that fails it won't send the transaction. If you want to \"force\" it to send the transaction that will revert, you need to set a fixed gas limit: `someContract.fun(arg1, arg2, { gasLimit: 1000000 })`\r\n\r\nIf you have more questions related to this, please use [our Discord server](https://hardhat.org/discord). And if you think there's some bug here, or if there's a feature you'd like to request, please submit a new issue.",
